data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` tree **won't compile** because the overload now takes `Func<ŌĆ”>` instead of `Expression<Func<ŌĆ”>>`.

**Fix** ŌĆö replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more expression tree plumbing needed.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö two changes

**a) Sibling properties are now uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column silently; EF 10 appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). If you have an existing database, add explicit column names to preserve the old schema:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> Both of these generate new migrations if left unaddressed, and the column rename can break existing queries/data.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging).

**Fix:**

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText (redacted) for logging,
        // command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
    }
}
```

Add the same parameter to every other method you implement (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
